anthropogenic forcing.

130
00:05:37,260 --> 00:05:39,500
Forcing is another word for

131
00:05:39,500 --> 00:05:41,675
the effect of our emissions

132
00:05:41,675 --> 00:05:43,880
on the temperature
that's observed.

133
00:05:43,880 --> 00:05:46,370
The observed warming
globally we can

134
00:05:46,370 --> 00:05:49,055
see is a little bit more
than half a degree Celsius,

135
00:05:49,055 --> 00:05:50,620
that's this black bar,

136
00:05:50,620 --> 00:05:53,555
and greenhouse gases, actually,

137
00:05:53,555 --> 00:05:56,570
through our models are
predicted to lead to

138
00:05:56,570 --> 00:05:59,480
a greater increase in
temperature than is observed.

139
00:05:59,480 --> 00:06:03,230
But the reason for
that is that we also,

140
00:06:03,230 --> 00:06:05,929
as humans, emit other particles

141
00:06:05,929 --> 00:06:08,570
and pollutants and emissions
into the atmosphere,

142
00:06:08,570 --> 00:06:09,890
and so those forcings

143
00:06:09,890 --> 00:06:11,800
actually end up cooling
the atmosphere,

144
00:06:11,800 --> 00:06:14,165
and when we add the green
bar and the yellow bar,

145
00:06:14,165 --> 00:06:16,610
we get our combined
anthropogenic forcings,

146
00:06:16,610 --> 00:06:18,695
which is matching our
observed warming.

147
00:06:18,695 --> 00:06:20,270
Something else to
note here is that

148
00:06:20,270 --> 00:06:23,810
the natural forcings due
to solar oscillations or

149
00:06:23,810 --> 00:06:26,270
any other aspects of
our orbit are much

150
00:06:26,270 --> 00:06:27,350
smaller compared to

151
00:06:27,350 --> 00:06:30,010
the observed warming and
the predicted warming.

152
00:06:30,010 --> 00:06:32,030
In terms of thinking
of the climate

153
00:06:32,030 --> 00:06:33,380
change impacts so far,

154
00:06:33,380 --> 00:06:35,615
it can be hard to attribute

155
00:06:35,615 --> 00:06:36,860
any given impact of

156
00:06:36,860 --> 00:06:39,250
climate change because of
the probabilities involved.

157
00:06:39,250 --> 00:06:41,135
But in recent decades,

158
00:06:41,135 --> 00:06:43,550
scientists have been
publishing studies that

159
00:06:43,550 --> 00:06:47,240
directly can link
climate change to

160
00:06:47,240 --> 00:06:50,270
specific impacts and they've
connected climate change

161
00:06:50,270 --> 00:06:53,375
to impacts on every single
continent in the world.

162
00:06:53,375 --> 00:06:54,955
That's what this is showing us.

163
00:06:54,955 --> 00:06:57,260
These impacts are happening
all over the world and

164
00:06:57,260 --> 00:07:00,095
they're connecting
all types of impacts.

165
00:07:00,095 --> 00:07:03,260
In blue, we've got impacts
