temperature change.

206
00:08:41,830 --> 00:08:43,515
If we make no change,

207
00:08:43,515 --> 00:08:47,250
8,000 would correspond to 4-5
degrees Celsius increase.

208
00:08:47,250 --> 00:08:51,185
But as we reduce our
cumulative CO_2 emissions,

209
00:08:51,185 --> 00:08:56,570
that would reduce the global
mean temperature change.

210
00:08:56,570 --> 00:08:59,570
Then finally, we can
link this to Panel A,

211
00:08:59,570 --> 00:09:01,415
the risks from climate change

212
00:09:01,415 --> 00:09:04,250
because these are dependent
on the temperature change.

213
00:09:04,250 --> 00:09:07,040
What we can see is
that for things like

214
00:09:07,040 --> 00:09:08,870
unique and threatened ecosystems

215
00:09:08,870 --> 00:09:10,700
or for extreme weather events,

216
00:09:10,700 --> 00:09:13,760
even at 1.5-2 degrees Celsius,

217
00:09:13,760 --> 00:09:15,590
which we were already
pretty much at,

218
00:09:15,590 --> 00:09:18,960
we're experiencing very high
risk due to climate change.

219
00:09:18,960 --> 00:09:22,400
But for things like the
